OL,3,CCrimes of necrophiliac killer Fuller
OL,4,C'could be repeated', inquiry finds
OL,6,F"I have therefore come to the
OL,7,Fconclusion that the current
OL,8,Farrangements for the regulation and
OL,9,Foversight of the care of people after
OL,10,Fdeath are partial, ineffective and, in
OL,11,Fsignificant areas, completely absent.
OL,13,F"I have asked myself whether there
OL,14,Fcould be a recurrence of the appalling
OL,15,Fcrimes committed by David Fuller.
OL,17,F"I have concluded that yes, it is
OL,18,Fentirely possible that such offences
OL,19,Fcould be repeated, particularly in
OL,20,Fthose sectors that lack any form of
OL,21,Fstatutory regulation."
