OL,6,FSir Jonathan said the Government
OL,7,F"must" introduce statutory regulations
OL,8,Fto protect the "security and dignity"
OL,9,Fof people after death.
OL,11,FThere was "little regard" given to who
OL,12,Fwas accessing the mortuary, with
OL,13,FFuller visiting 444 times in a year `
OL,14,Fsomething that went "unnoticed and
OL,15,Funchecked", the inquiry found.
OL,17,FThen in October last year inquiry
OL,18,Fchairman Sir Jonathan Michael called
OL,19,Ffor urgent regulation of the funeral
OL,20,Findustry, which he called an
OL,21,F"unregulated free-for-all".
